164
00:05:32.360 --> 00:05:36.800
Input - Typing, Writing and Clicking

165
00:05:37.840 --> 00:05:42.160
When content is accessible, people can 
use a variety of hardware and software

166
00:05:42.160 --> 00:05:44.400
to enter text and activate commands.

167
00:05:45.520 --> 00:05:47.720
Some people do not use keyboards

168
00:05:47.720 --> 00:05:50.040
and use only pointing devices instead.

169
00:05:50.280 --> 00:05:52.280
This could include a specialised mouse,

170
00:05:52.280 --> 00:05:53.880
joystick, trackball,

171
00:05:54.040 --> 00:05:58.440
or touch screen to click links and buttons
and to type on on-screen keyboards.

172
00:05:58.440 --> 00:06:00.520
However, even when using these tools,

173
00:06:00.520 --> 00:06:01.920
people might have difficulty

174
00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:03.480
selecting small targets,

175
00:06:03.480 --> 00:06:06.280
such as small links, buttons and controls.

176
00:06:06.640 --> 00:06:10.240
Websites and apps with large
clickable areas around checkboxes,

177
00:06:10.440 --> 00:06:12.520
radio buttons, and other controls,

178
00:06:12.520 --> 00:06:14.040
are easier to use for people

179
00:06:14.040 --> 00:06:15.320
with limited mobility

180
00:06:15.320 --> 00:06:16.800
and reduced dexterity.

181
00:06:18.080 --> 00:06:20.600
Websites and apps also
need to provide support

182
00:06:20.600 --> 00:06:22.560
for people who use the keyboard only.

183
00:06:23.200 --> 00:06:26.280
This includes providing ways
to skip over repeated content,

184
00:06:26.280 --> 00:06:29.720
such as headers and navigation bars, 
as well as not breaking the default

185
00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:32.880
functionality in browsers
and operating systems.

186
00:06:33.000 --> 00:06:33.960
For example,

187
00:06:33.960 --> 00:06:35.800
using the Tab key to move around

188
00:06:35.800 --> 00:06:37.440
clickable items in the content,

189
00:06:37.440 --> 00:06:39.720
using the Enter key for selecting items,

190
00:06:39.720 --> 00:06:42.160
and making the currently active item visible

191
00:06:42.160 --> 00:06:44.520
by showing a rectangular box around it.

192
00:06:44.520 --> 00:06:47.880
Websites and apps that provide
word prediction and accelerators,

193
00:06:47.880 --> 00:06:49.640
for example for search terms,

194
00:06:49.640 --> 00:06:51.320
reduce the amount of typing,

195
00:06:51.320 --> 00:06:52.720
and make them more efficient

196
00:06:52.720 --> 00:06:54.000
for keyboard users.

197
00:06:55.320 --> 00:06:59.080
Additionally, not everyone using
only the keyboard can see the screen;

198
00:06:59.080 --> 00:07:01.600
for example, people who are blind.

199
00:07:01.600 --> 00:07:04.600
So, in addition to
ensuring keyboard support,

200
00:07:04.600 --> 00:07:07.840
websites and apps also need
to provide clear instructions, 

201
00:07:07.840 --> 00:07:12.160
labels for form controls, error
messages, and status notifications,

202
00:07:12.520 --> 00:07:14.840
so that people know what
is happening on the screen.

203
00:07:15.360 --> 00:07:19.200
Websites and apps need to help people
find and correct mistakes in their input;

204
00:07:19.600 --> 00:07:23.000
for example, by showing a summary
of the entered data before submitting it.

205
00:07:23.440 --> 00:07:26.440
They also need to provide sufficient
time to complete tasks,

206
00:07:26.760 --> 00:07:28.960
or avoid timing limitations altogether.

207
00:07:29.560 --> 00:07:32.480
Many people with disabilities
require more time to navigate

208
00:07:32.480 --> 00:07:35.560
and orient themselves in the
content, and to click and type.

209
00:07:36.040 --> 00:07:39.200
In particular, people with cognitive
and learning disabilities.

210
00:07:40.200 --> 00:07:44.400
Finally, websites and apps also need
to consider people who do not use

211
00:07:44.400 --> 00:07:47.800
keyboard or pointing devices at all,
and use speech input instead.

212
00:07:48.240 --> 00:07:51.400
For example, websites and apps
need to be programmed and designed

213
00:07:51.480 --> 00:07:52.760
so that the name of a button

214
00:07:52.760 --> 00:07:55.920
in the software code matches
the name displayed to the user.

215
00:07:56.680 --> 00:07:57.960
Click send email.

