218
00:08:09.600 --> 00:08:12.600
Interaction - navigation and finding

219
00:08:14.480 --> 00:08:16.400
When content is accessible,

220
00:08:16.400 --> 00:08:18.480
people can navigate and find information

221
00:08:18.480 --> 00:08:20.760
using different strategies and approaches

222
00:08:20.760 --> 00:08:22.280
depending on their preferences,

223
00:08:22.280 --> 00:08:25.160
skills and abilities.

224
00:08:25.160 --> 00:08:26.920
Many people with cognitive

225
00:08:26.920 --> 00:08:28.280
and learning disabilities

226
00:08:28.280 --> 00:08:30.160
rely on clear layout and design

227
00:08:30.160 --> 00:08:33.280
to find information on websites and apps.

228
00:08:33.280 --> 00:08:34.400
This includes different ways

229
00:08:34.400 --> 00:08:35.960
of navigating the content,

230
00:08:35.960 --> 00:08:37.840
such as using hierarchical menus

231
00:08:37.840 --> 00:08:39.760
as well as search functionality;

232
00:08:39.760 --> 00:08:41.280
with visual orientation cues,

233
00:08:41.280 --> 00:08:42.840
such as using background colors

234
00:08:42.840 --> 00:08:44.080
to indicate different parts

235
00:08:44.080 --> 00:08:45.120
of the content,

236
00:08:45.120 --> 00:08:46.640
using unique headings,

237
00:08:46.640 --> 00:08:48.080
and placing relevant information

238
00:08:48.080 --> 00:08:49.960
in prominent areas.

239
00:08:49.960 --> 00:08:51.360
It's also important to use

240
00:08:51.360 --> 00:08:53.600
a consistent and predictable design.

241
00:08:54.600 --> 00:08:56.880
While many of these are typically usability

242
00:08:56.880 --> 00:08:58.600
aspects that affect people with

243
00:08:58.600 --> 00:09:00.240
and without disabilities,

244
00:09:00.240 --> 00:09:01.480
these situations often

245
00:09:01.480 --> 00:09:04.680
affect people with disabilities to a greater extent.

246
00:09:04.680 --> 00:09:05.560
For example,

247
00:09:05.560 --> 00:09:06.560
people with low vision

248
00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:08.160
who use screen magnification

249
00:09:08.160 --> 00:09:10.800
also rely on visual orientation cues

250
00:09:10.800 --> 00:09:13.120
to orient themselves and find information

251
00:09:13.120 --> 00:09:14.520
on websites and apps.

252
00:09:15.480 --> 00:09:18.560
And consistency predictability helps everyone.

253
00:09:18.560 --> 00:09:19.240
For example,

254
00:09:19.240 --> 00:09:21.080
people who are blind use screen readers

255
00:09:21.080 --> 00:09:22.800
to scan the content structures,

256
00:09:22.800 --> 00:09:23.880
such as headings,

257
00:09:23.880 --> 00:09:25.760
links, and navigational menus

258
00:09:25.760 --> 00:09:28.360
to get an overview and orient themselves.

259
00:09:28.360 --> 00:09:29.920
Websites and apps with clear

260
00:09:29.920 --> 00:09:31.280
and consistent headings,

261
00:09:31.280 --> 00:09:33.040
labels and structures

262
00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:33.800
make the content

263
00:09:33.800 --> 00:09:36.200
more predictable and easier to navigate.

264
00:09:37.960 --> 00:09:39.040
In addition,

265
00:09:39.040 --> 00:09:41.040
people who are blind rely on mechanisms

266
00:09:41.040 --> 00:09:42.960
to skip over blocks of content,

267
00:09:42.960 --> 00:09:44.040
such as headings,

268
00:09:44.040 --> 00:09:45.080
navigation bars,

269
00:09:45.080 --> 00:09:46.000
or menus,

270
00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:48.520
repeated within websites and apps.

271
00:09:48.520 --> 00:09:50.840
They also rely on websites and apps to provide

272
00:09:50.840 --> 00:09:52.040
clear instructions

273
00:09:52.040 --> 00:09:53.520
and help users identify

274
00:09:53.520 --> 00:09:54.840
and correct mistakes,

275
00:09:54.840 --> 00:09:56.200
such as incorrect dates,

276
00:09:56.200 --> 00:09:58.360
numbers and other input.

277
00:09:59.440 --> 00:10:00.400
In addition,

278
00:10:00.400 --> 00:10:02.040
people with physical disabilities

279
00:10:02.040 --> 00:10:04.440
rely on consistent labels which allow browsers

280
00:10:04.440 --> 00:10:07.320
to optionally remember previous entries.

281
00:10:07.320 --> 00:10:08.640
This speeds up typing

282
00:10:08.640 --> 00:10:10.800
because people can select previous entries,

283
00:10:10.800 --> 00:10:13.480
for example, names and addresses.

